Kung Fu Hamster wrote:Semi On wrote:Kung Fu Hamster wrote:FINALLY managed to get a sitter for Friday night and our tickets purchased. I wanted to go try one of the fancy movie theaters that also has a full bar & restaurant service, but they (iPic Scottsdale AZ) wanted $56 for a pair of tickets, and their dinner menu was ridiculous.Maybe in the future it'd be a good date night spot, but not right now.Studio Movie Grill is about the price of a regular movie theater and still has a full bar and dinner service. The food isn't bad, but not quite as high end as iPic. However, they have a call button on the seat and can bring you drinks throughout the entire flick. iPic only serves for the first fifteen minutes or so, if I recall.That's where we're headed. We went there to see The Hobbit, and I wanted to try iPic for comparison. After seeing the price tag, however...It's nicer, but the regular seats, while plush, don't recline which was kind of uncomfortable and the lack of mid-movie cocktails was a turn off. I definitely don't think it's worth the cost, which is why we haven't been back since.
