Posted: Wed May 15, 2013 1:16 am
I saw this last night as well.
Spoiler: show
While I enjoyed most of the movie, it was rather ruined for me with the whole reactor bullshit. I was actually quite pleased that they had stayed away from WOK and Space Seed largely (except for the line forever ruined by Transformers 3) until the reactor. I liked the initial Tribble cameo, as it was subtle but I did spot instantly that Khan's blood was a "get out of jail free card". I also liked the fact that while Pine was "channeling" Shatner, his Kirk was different. He is more reckless, too inexperienced (that was actually the thing I hated about the first film - he would never have gotten command that quickly). All the characters being slightly different helps.The moment Scotty runs up to Kirk and tells him the reactor is dead, out of alignment etc I knew with 100% certainty how the rest of the movie would go. I was not wrong. I was however disappointed.Now, I'm sure those who haven't seen WOK 50 million times will enjoy it, but me? No. Especially the moment New Spock screams KKHHHAAANNNNN!!!! I just wish they hadn't gone there, because it was never going to beat/replace/improve on the original scene. We aren't as invested in these characters as the originals and it was OBVIOUS they wouldn't let Kirk die. They had set up his resurrection already, and that just removed any emotion of "OMG they killed Kirk" that I might have had. It was well acted, but it was just wrong.Whereas with WOK, I was stunned that they killed Spock. Stunned. And it wasn't obvious (until ST3 was announced/released) that Spock would come back.Cumberbatch was awesome. Really rather good. They didn't make enough use of Robocop though, that was a shame. Pike dying was a surprise, I didn't expect him to go - it does mean we won't get The Cage/The Menagerie however.The Section 31 reference was interesting and obviously aimed squarely at the original fan, as they only really turned up in DS9 and then Enterprise so any "new" watchers wouldn't really know what was being referred to. I had pretty much guessed it was going to be related to Section 31 pretty early on.
