The way movie releases work in the US now confuses me. It used to be a single date with midnight showings for big enough movies.Now, there's a release date. But two days before that, some people can get passes for sneak previews and the day before, you can catch showings that start between 9-11 PM. But not midnight. Then the film opens the next day for realsies.I'll probably catch one of the showings that start between 9-11 PM tomorrow night.Also, it's been a mistake to even open this thread, because I've managed to spoil myself on shit without opening spoiler tags. So yay to that.
