Quote:The way movie releases work in the US now confuses me. It used to be a single date with midnight showings for big enough movies.++ I was talking to my wife about this subject this weekend. We were at a mall on a Thursday night a month or so back, and there were two giant lines for movies coming out on Friday. We were thinking they were for midnight showings, but both had 8 PM showings that night, since apparently it's too much to ask for Friday release movies to actually wait until Friday to be shown. This led to a "back in my day, if you wanted see a midnight showing, you actually had to stay up past midnight" cranky old person talk between us. It came up this weekend again because we were planning when to watch this movie, knowing that it "opens" on Friday, but showings today were cropping up in our search. We were thinking that it was another "Thursday midnight showing, but not really midnight" deal, but then realized that the date was Wednesday, and trying to figure out how movies getting released on a Friday are now getting shown on Wednesdays.Also, yeah, I'm pretty much having to not look at the internet at all now. I was going to check out an AICN review of the movie, and it started out basically like "Here's a review, there's going to be some spoilers in it, and by the way, here's one now!" I got kind of pissed. It's one thing to have a review and say something like "Spoilers after this point". It's another thing entirely to launch into a spoiler in the same breath as your warning that you're going to spoil stuff.
