Alright, here's what we're going to do as a compromise. Please note that I'm not posting this in Tyranny Yellowâ„¢. This isn't an official moderator directive. Speaking for only myself, I hate playing spoiler police. So I hope we don't have to lay down an actual "rules" here and everyone will just play nicely.How about this? Let's keep wrapping spoilers for Star Trek Into Darkness until Monday (5/20). I have to assume that anyone who's a big enough Star Trek fan to want to avoid having to staying out of this thread (or to care that much about having the movie spoiled for them in the first place) is also going to be a big enough Star Trek fan to see the new movie during its opening weekend (in North America).After Monday, all's fair. If you haven't had a chance to see the movie and you don't want it spoiled, steer clear of the thread starting on Monday.I definitely don't want to start a dedicated thread for Star Trek Into Darkness, for the simple reason that the new movie is obviously going to be the dominant topic in the Trekosphere for the foreseeable future. Telling people to re-post their STID questions and comments in the new thread would get old, fast. It makes sense to me to keep it all in one place.Does that sound agreeable?
