Posted: Wed May 15, 2013 9:17 pm
Just came back from the 8pm IMAX showing of Into Darkness, and... Spoiler: show
KHHHHHHHHAAAAAAAAAAAAAANNNNNNNNNNNNNN!!! Cumberbatch was fucking fantastic and the movie was a blast. Some things were a bit obvious and telegraphed, but it didn't make it any less fun when it happened. They really focused on the interaction/relationship between Spock/Kirk, regrettably at the cost of a lot of screen time for the rest of the crew (save for sexy Zoe). I felt like they kept a good bit of humor, a good bit of suspense, and further expanded the new Trek universe while keeping some things ready to go for the next film (read: Klingons).We all greatly enjoyed the movie, and I got a cool new poster for my cubicle, too!
As far as the IMAX quality itself, I think it's my local theater, but there was a decent bit of ghosting throughout the film, especially on strongly back-lit scenes. Other than that the 3D was strong and used to good effect at times. However after experiencing the Hobbit in HFR 3D, it's hard to go back to 24fps 3D, even at IMAX sizes. It's just really jarring at times due to the shitty framerate.
