I liked it. Quite a bit. It's flawed though, mostly by a pretty major plot hole near the end of the movie that colored my opinion of the scenes immediately following it. But the rest of the movie was good enough that I was able to let go and move on.But hey, plot holes and deus ex machina are nothing new to Star Trek. I don't understand how people who throw fits about that stuff can watch any Trek in the first place, let alone justify crapping on newer stuff just because it's new while aggrandizing something else that's just as flawed.I'm not sure where I'd rank it overall on the ST movie pantheon. But it's near the top. It's not first. It's probably not second. But third or fourth wouldn't be off the mark. Even if they hadn't stumbled it never would have been first. But it could have been a solid second if not for the aforementioned problem.The ending made me wish they could just take that cast and make a TV show with them.AnejoDave wrote:
Spoiler: show
