Posted: Thu May 16, 2013 7:24 pm
I've officially seen in three times now, and I'm done...for a while, at least. I'm sure I'll see it at least once or twice more before it leaves the theater.Aside from my "it's 2/3rds of a great movie" remark, the only other thing I'll say is that of the three formats (IMAX 3D, 2D and Real 3D), I didn't think any of them had a significant advantage over the others. The size of the IMAX screen was nice, but the 3D in both that format and the Real 3D format was really subtle for the most part. I noticed the lens flare more when I watched it in Real 3D, but that was also the third time I'd seen the movie in 24 hours--so I was probably subconsciously paying more attention to things like that.My stubs:They also gave us a souvenir poster at the "fan sneak" last night:I'm writing my review right now (taking a short break for a late dinner), and plan to submit it just a bit later tonight. I will naturally be back to plug it when they post it on the front page Jonathon
