Deviation wrote:I'm not sure where I'd rank it overall on the ST movie pantheon. But it's near the top. It's not first. It's probably not second. But third or fourth wouldn't be off the mark. Even if they hadn't stumbled it never would have been first. But it could have been a solid second if not for the aforementioned problem.I'd put it at fourth or fifth, depending on how you rank VI and First Contact.Just got back from seeing it. If releasing on Thursday was their idea to improve sales... well, bit of a failure on that end. There were a total of 11 people in the theater, including me. A little weird, seeing a new release with that few people in the room.Don't really have anything to say that hasn't already been said. Although... Benedict Cumberbatch. Holy crap. That man is incredible.
